<div
style="
max-width:700px;
margin:auto;
"
>

<div class="card">

<div style="
display:flex;
align-items:center;
gap:15px;
margin-bottom:25px;
">

<div style="
width:60px;
height:60px;
border-radius:16px;
background:#e7fff0;
display:flex;
align-items:center;
justify-content:center;
font-size:24px;
color:#0c5f2c;
">

<i class="fas fa-user-shield"></i>

</div>

<div>

<h2>
Invite New Admin
</h2>

<p style="
color:#666;
margin-top:6px;
">
Only super administrators can invite admins.
</p>

</div>

</div>

<form
action="/admin/invite-admin"
method="POST"
>

<div class="form-group">

<label>
Admin Email
</label>

<input
type="email"
name="email"
class="form-control"
placeholder="Enter admin email"
required
/>

</div>

<div style="
background:#f7faf9;
padding:18px;
border-radius:14px;
margin-bottom:25px;
border-left:5px solid #0c5f2c;
">

<h4 style="
margin-bottom:10px;
color:#0c5f2c;
">
How It Works
</h4>

<p style="
line-height:1.7;
color:#555;
">

When this email is added into the system,
the next signup using this email will
automatically receive the
<strong>admin</strong> role.

</p>

</div>

<div style="
display:flex;
gap:15px;
flex-wrap:wrap;
">

<button class="btn btn-green">

<i class="fas fa-paper-plane"></i>
Invite Admin

</button>

<a
href="/admin/admins"
class="btn"
style="
background:#eee;
color:#333;
"
>

Cancel

</a>

</div>

</form>

</div>

</div>